$msg = "Append the Smart Meter read-out to this response, per the smart-meter skill. Output a single line: Confidence NN% | bar BB% (reversible or irreversible) then clears or BELOW, then a model tag ' | model: X' and an effort tag ' | effort: Y', both driven by the SAME stakes classification so they never disagree: Haiku/low for routine/mechanical/read-only/bulk work, Sonnet/medium for normal implementation, Opus/high for high-stakes/irreversible/ambiguous work or whenever the score is below its bar. Both are the recommended tier for the current task, so the user can compare against what they are actually running (same desktop UI picker for both) and switch if needed. Auto-expand the full assessment block only when the score is below its bar or when the user explicitly asks. Applies to every response."
@{hookSpecificOutput = @{hookEventName = 'UserPromptSubmit'; additionalContext = $msg}} | ConvertTo-Json -Compress -Depth 4
